Economist says NYMEX light crude could hit $ 30 . The price of New York Mercantile Exchange ( NYMEX ) light crude may soar to $ 30 following news of the U . S . military ' s cruise missile strike against air - defence targets in Iraq on Tuesday , said Kazuaki Kondo , a senior economist at the Japanese Institute of Middle Eastern Economies . Kondo , who was speaking on a Reuters Financial Television programme , did not give a time frame . NYMEX crude oil for October rose 22 cents to $ 23 . 70 shortly after the Pentagon announced that the United States had launched the missiles . 
